The paper deals with the problem of finding a minimum multicut in an embedded graph with a fixed number of terminals. This problem is related to graph theory, algorithms, and computational geometry, which are covered by the sub-categories cs.DS, cs.CG, and cs.GT. The paper also uses topological techniques and computations in covering spaces, which are related to algebraic topology and computational topology, covered by the sub-categories cs.DM and cs.SI.
